Package streams

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Function<E,F>
    Specify an interface for a Function type to pass as argument to Stream#map.
    Operator<F,E>
    Specify an interface for an Operator type to pass as argument to Stream#reduce and Stream#fold.
    Predicate<E>
    Specify an interface for a Predicate type to pass as argument to Stream#select.
    Stream<E>
    Stream defines a wrapper for the Iterable interface and adds four useful functions to apply and chain operations on iterators.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractStream<E>
    Abstract class which provides a skeleton implementation of Stream.
    Streams
    A static helper class for the Stream interface.
